<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB04728</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT MANDATING MORE STRINGENT POLICY ON GRANTING INDIVIDUALS PERMIT TO CARRY FIREARMS AND PRESCRIBING PENALTIES FOR VIOLATION THEREOF</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Enumerates several series of tests and seminars that an individual should pass in order to be eligible
to be granted permit to carry a firearm such as neuropsychiatric test; seminars on anger management, firearm safety, safe gun handling etiquette, proper handgun maintenance, situational awareness; and marksmanship training.

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : "Strict Regulation for Securing Permit to Carry a Firearm Act"</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>CASTELO, PRECIOUS HIPOLITO</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-09-20</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON PUBLIC ORDER AND SAFETY ON 2019-09-24</td></tr></table>